_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟡 Minor_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Cleanup setTimeout on unmount.**

The `setTimeout` in `handleCopyAddress` can cause warnings or potential memory leaks if the component unmounts before the 2-second timer completes. Store the timeout ID and clear it in a `useEffect` cleanup.




<details>
<summary>🛡️ Proposed fix</summary>

```diff
+import { useRef, useEffect } from 'react';
+
 export function OnboardingAdventurePage() {
   const t = useTranslations('OnboardingAdventure');
   // ... other hooks
+  const timeoutRef = useRef<NodeJS.Timeout | null>(null);

+  useEffect(() => {
+    return () => {
+      if (timeoutRef.current) clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
+    };
+  }, []);
+
   const handleCopyAddress = (address: string) => {
     copyToClipboard(address);
     setCopiedAddress(true);
-    window.setTimeout(() => setCopiedAddress(false), 2000);
+    if (timeoutRef.current) clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
+    timeoutRef.current = setTimeout(() => setCopiedAddress(false), 2000);
   };
```
</details>

