**Reset copied-state when deposit selection context changes.**

`copiedAddress` is shared state, so switching deposit spaces can briefly show “copied” for an address that was never copied in the new context.



<details>
<summary>💡 Suggested fix</summary>

```diff
   const handleDepositSpaceChange = (next: string) => {
     setDepositSpaceSlug(next);
     setDepositDetailsSpaceSlug('');
+    setCopiedAddress(false);
   };

@@
           onQueryChange: (next) => {
             setDepositQuery(next);
             setDepositSpaceSlug('');
             setDepositDetailsSpaceSlug('');
+            setCopiedAddress(false);
           },

@@
           onAction: () => {
             if (!depositSpaceSlug) return;
+            setCopiedAddress(false);
             setDepositDetailsSpaceSlug(depositSpaceSlug);
           },
```
</details>


